<br>
I'd like to ask for some reccomendations for which server I should start on when I switch over to DAOC.   <br>
<br>
I love pvp, and I play on rallos zek now.  BUT I'm really tired of all the big pvp or pk guilds (you know who they are) and I want to avoid being on whatever server or servers they've chosen to play on.  I understand that on one server there's already a bit of a problem with griefers and on another some of the big ol pvp guilds have already closed out one of the frontiers, or something like that (don't know all that much about the game, this is just from what I've heard in EQ chat...).  Now this is a good thing, and it's what the game is for, but I'd rather not play where those guys are trying to &quot;rule&quot; and &quot;own jooz all&quot;--I've had enough of that for a lifetime on Rzek.<br>
<br>
Everyone from my old EQ guild has sort of split up, and as yet, I've no friends switching from EQ to daoc, so I'm free to go to any server.<br>
<br>
I'd like to find one with a good community, where realm vs realm conflict is roleplayed, if that exists.  And I'd also like to find one where some good people are playing, so I thought I'd ask some good people--you all ;P<br>
<br>
also, any suggestions as to whether I should play a celtic druid, or midgard archer?  Kinda like both...<br>
<br>
Oh, and I can't start the game for about 2 weeks--work sucks, ya know. <br>
<br>
thanks! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueckointhedarkness.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ecko in the darkness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/5/01 11:50:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=173.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reccomendations for server selection?</span><hr size=1>   Start in the newest and emptiest server you can find.  That or test server.   Kill stealing is rampant in the crowded easy to reach hunting spots, however, everyone excepts it very well.  I have not seen tempers flare yet because of this, mainly because you don't want to argue with a realm mate you'll be fighting besides the next night. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udasteel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dasteel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/6/01 1:24:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=173.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reccomendations for server selection?</span><hr size=1> I think most of the aggressive PK guilds jumped on early. A new server would probably be your best bet.<br>
<br>
/agree Ecko <p><i>It seemed like a good idea at the time ...</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umalbor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malbor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druid in Absentia<br>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/6/01 8:37:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=173.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/malbor/malbor.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reccomendations for server selection?</span><hr size=1> <br>
Merlin seemed to pick up alot of the UO leet Dewds playing midgard.  I'd avoid that server like the plague.<br>
<br>
Your best bet would definately be one of the newer servers.<br>
<br>
Also of note, preliminary results based on who is invading and holding territory is that Midgard seems to have the RVR power earliest.  Albion seems to be getting the largest number of people and Hibernia is getting smacked around alot by both Albion and Midgard.<br>
<br>
There could be alot of reasons for this and might change dramatically when Hibernia starts maturing.   It's possible that the hardcore powerlevellers went to Midgard, powered to 30 and started hunting greys :)<br>
<br>
-Mal<br>
